com.cyberfront.crdt.operations

Class DeleteOperation

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.cyberfront.crdt.operations.AbstractOperation
      • com.cyberfront.crdt.operations.DeleteOperation
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable<AbstractOperation>

    public class DeleteOperation
extends AbstractOperation
    The DeleteOperation encapsulates the deletion of a JSON document in the CRDT. It should have the highest timestamp of any operation contained in the CRDT. An RFC 6902 formated JSON object isn't used here, instead the operation is held as null and null is returned when processing the operations. This eliminates the possibility of making any changes to the the object subsequent to the processing of a DeleteOperation, even though there may be subsequent operations with higher timestamp values contained in the CRDT.
